---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Clear Human Intervention Points"
  description="Make it obvious when and where users can step in, review, modify, or override AI behavior—so they know they can intervene at any point, not just approve final results."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Clear intervention points" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Visible Review Steps</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Step 1: AI suggests draft → [Review & Edit] Step 2: AI refines → [Review & Edit] Step
            3: Final → [Approve]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Each step shows a clear "Review & Edit" option; users can intervene at any point.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Inline Edit Controls</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI-generated text appears with [Edit] buttons on each paragraph. Users can modify any
            part without rejecting the whole.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Intervention is granular and immediate; no need to wait until the end.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"
              ><b>Hidden or End-Only Intervention (Problematic)</b></mds-text
            >
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI runs through all steps automatically; users only see "Approve" or "Reject" at the
            very end. No way to intervene mid-process or edit specific parts.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Users can't catch errors early or guide the AI; they must accept or reject everything.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Show clear "Review", "Edit", or "Modify" options at each step where users can intervene.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Hide intervention points or only offer approve/reject at the very end of the process.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Make intervention granular—let users edit specific parts (e.g. paragraphs, sections) without
      rejecting the whole output.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Force all-or-nothing approval; avoid making users wait until completion to intervene.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
